<p><span>Eng.  César Paredes Piana (Peru) has an Engineer degree in  Agriculture from  the College of Agriculture of the Catholic University  of Perú. He is  presently the Head of the Peruvian National Institute of  Agrarian  Innovation (INIA). Previously, Eng. Paredes served as the  Regional  Manager for Hortus S.A.C., which markets agricultural products  in Peru,  and as Consultant/Advisor for ACM Peru S.A.C., an  agribusiness  consulting and management firm. Having served in various  capacities at  Peru’s Ministry of Agriculture and Ministry of the  Presidency, Eng.  Paredes has extensive experience in the governmental  and agricultural  sectors of Peru.</span></p>